1
00:00:00,438 --> 00:00:02,445
Younes Basil
Muhammad, from Mosul

2
00:00:02,750 --> 00:00:04,789
I neither study nor work

3
00:00:07,078 --> 00:00:08,359
They detained me once

4
00:00:09,250 --> 00:00:10,352
They came and took
me from the house

5
00:00:10,781 --> 00:00:13,227
That was because my uncle
belonged to the intelligence service

6
00:00:14,093 --> 00:00:15,093
They confiscated his house

7
00:00:15,836 --> 00:00:17,055
And seized the belongings

8
00:00:17,859 --> 00:00:18,914
Meaning they became theirs

9
00:00:19,414 --> 00:00:21,945
When I came to take the
belongings, they considered me a thief

10
00:00:23,640 --> 00:00:25,953
Interviewer: Did you come to take the house
belongings after they had written “confiscated” on it?

11
00:00:26,406 --> 00:00:29,453
After they wrote on the house that it was
confiscated, I went in to take the belongings

12
00:00:32,469 --> 00:00:34,984
Interviewer: Do you remember the
month and year you were detained?

13
00:00:35,009 --> 00:00:37,859
Also the circumstances of your
detention — was it in winter or summer?

14
00:00:38,039 --> 00:00:40,648
Did it happen in the afternoon or at sunset? And
how did they come to take you from the house?

15
00:00:42,453 --> 00:00:43,523
They came to me in the morning

16
00:00:46,375 --> 00:00:48,117
They came to my family’s house

17
00:00:48,391 --> 00:00:49,391
And I wasn’t there then

18
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:50,960
I was at my friend’s

19
00:00:51,859 --> 00:00:52,891
And when I returned home

20
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:57,516
My mother told me then that ISIS
had come to the house looking for me

21
00:00:58,578 --> 00:00:59,492
And they asked about me

22
00:01:00,484 --> 00:01:01,953
I asked her the reason,
but she didn’t know

23
00:01:04,179 --> 00:01:07,992
I sat with my mother for
about fifteen to thirty minutes

24
00:01:08,648 --> 00:01:10,852
Then they came again to
the house a second time

25
00:01:11,852 --> 00:01:14,555
They knocked on the door and asked
for me, so I went down to see them

26
00:01:14,688 --> 00:01:16,594
They asked me to go with
them to inquire about something

27
00:01:18,812 --> 00:01:19,813
And I went with them

28
00:01:20,297 --> 00:01:22,961
They took me to Dawasa Prison

29
00:01:23,531 --> 00:01:25,203
I spent about ten days there

30
00:01:25,914 --> 00:01:27,648
Then they transferred me to
the <i>Qaimaqam</i>Prison

31
00:01:28,656 --> 00:01:30,055
And from there
they brought me here

32
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:35,289
I spent here about one
month and twenty days

33
00:01:35,844 --> 00:01:37,078
After the twenty days

34
00:01:37,805 --> 00:01:40,820
They told me that I
had been released

35
00:01:42,421 --> 00:01:44,742
They took me to the
<i>hisba</i> [religious police] car

36
00:01:45,484 --> 00:01:46,586
They prepared an
anesthetic injection for me

37
00:01:47,266 --> 00:01:49,461
And injected it into my arm

38
00:01:49,977 --> 00:01:51,820
And before the people’s
eyes, they cut off my hand

39
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:55,047
Interviewer: Was that after the
twenty-first day of your detention?

40
00:01:55,156 --> 00:01:57,703
No, after one month
and twenty days

41
00:02:00,492 --> 00:02:02,632
Interviewer: After they took you
from the house to Dawasa Prison

42
00:02:02,657 --> 00:02:04,164
Did they imprison
you there or here?

43
00:02:04,258 --> 00:02:06,773
They imprisoned me there,
then transferred me here

44
00:02:06,961 --> 00:02:08,672
Interviewer: Did they transfer you
here after they amputated your hand?

45
00:02:08,906 --> 00:02:10,859
No, before that

46
00:02:11,047 --> 00:02:12,047
They brought me here

47
00:02:12,281 --> 00:02:14,125
Interviewer: Tell me about the
conditions of your arrival at this place.

48
00:02:14,617 --> 00:02:15,727
What time was it?

49
00:02:15,921 --> 00:02:17,406
Was it in the
afternoon or at sunset?

50
00:02:17,445 --> 00:02:19,688
And was it winter or summer?

51
00:02:20,305 --> 00:02:23,922
Who came with you? And were your
eyes blindfolded or your hands shackled?

52
00:02:24,453 --> 00:02:25,969
My hands were shackled

53
00:02:27,375 --> 00:02:28,516
And my eyes were blindfolded

54
00:02:29,609 --> 00:02:32,813
There were about five
or six detainees with me

55
00:02:32,859 --> 00:02:34,664
But their charges were different

56
00:02:36,031 --> 00:02:38,031
They brought me here
around two in the afternoon

57
00:02:39,227 --> 00:02:42,078
They transferred me
from the prison to here

58
00:02:44,688 --> 00:02:45,555
Interviewer: Which
prison do you mean?

59
00:02:45,820 --> 00:02:46,781
Dawasa Prison

60
00:02:49,414 --> 00:02:54,430
Interviewer: How many ISIS
members were accompanying you?

61
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:56,547
Do you remember their
names or nationalities?

62
00:02:57,421 --> 00:02:59,703
I don’t remember their
names or what they looked like

63
00:02:59,728 --> 00:03:02,477
But there were about six
men who brought us here

64
00:03:03,039 --> 00:03:05,641
Interviewer: When you
reached this entrance

65
00:03:05,666 --> 00:03:07,406
The church that
had become a prison

66
00:03:08,453 --> 00:03:10,930
Interviewer: Did they
blindfold your eyes?

67
00:03:11,266 --> 00:03:12,461
Yes, my eyes were blindfolded

68
00:03:12,486 --> 00:03:13,258
Interviewer: And your
hands were shackled?

69
00:03:13,283 --> 00:03:13,844
Yes

70
00:03:14,383 --> 00:03:16,882
Interviewer: Had you heard of this
prison or know anything about it before?

71
00:03:17,281 --> 00:03:23,344
No, I had heard of the <i>Hisba</i>,
but I didn’t know what it was

72
00:03:24,711 --> 00:03:28,391
Interviewer: You didn’t know that this church
had been turned into a prison and held prisoners?

73
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:31,742
No, I thought it was
just a regular house

74
00:03:32,531 --> 00:03:35,172
And they used it for
flogging or punishing people

75
00:03:35,289 --> 00:03:36,367
And then they would release them

76
00:03:36,734 --> 00:03:37,961
I didn’t think it was a prison

77
00:03:46,086 --> 00:03:49,820
Interviewer: How did you and the people with
you feel when you arrived at this entrance?

78
00:03:50,195 --> 00:03:52,508
What did you feel, and what
thoughts went through your mind?

79
00:03:54,578 --> 00:03:57,406
I was very afraid

80
00:03:58,148 --> 00:04:00,891
I was scared they would kill me
even though I hadn’t done anything

81
00:04:02,484 --> 00:04:04,445
When I arrived they took
me in through this door

82
00:04:06,313 --> 00:04:10,273
They led me in with
five or six other people

83
00:04:10,687 --> 00:04:11,687
Interviewer: Where
did they take you?

84
00:04:12,109 --> 00:04:12,844
From here?

85
00:04:12,869 --> 00:04:14,226
Yes, we came from
here and they led us in

86
00:04:15,078 --> 00:04:18,086
There were prisoners inside

87
00:04:18,648 --> 00:04:21,570
And the ISIS members
were flogging them

88
00:04:22,352 --> 00:04:25,055
Some were brought here for
smoking cigarettes or for mobile phones

89
00:04:26,492 --> 00:04:31,773
Others for writing slogans
like Long live Iraq on the walls

90
00:04:34,156 --> 00:04:37,164
So they led us into the hall

91
00:04:37,953 --> 00:04:40,477
Interviewer: Today, when you look
at the entrance you’re standing next to

92
00:04:40,914 --> 00:04:43,828
What has changed in this entrance,
whether in features or appearance?

93
00:04:44,453 --> 00:04:47,383
Since the time ISIS was here
until today, what has changed?

94
00:04:47,408 --> 00:04:50,000
While standing here, do old
feelings come back to you?

95
00:04:50,025 --> 00:04:52,469
Or do you feel that you’ve
become a free person?

96
00:04:53,195 --> 00:04:57,781
When I came here I remembered
my hand and wished it were still here

97
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:03,836
Interviewer: Do you feel that the
entrance’s appearance has changed?

98
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:05,781
And has the place and your memories
of it changed, or is it still the same?

99
00:05:05,914 --> 00:05:06,859
It’s still the same

100
00:05:11,992 --> 00:05:17,305
Interviewer: Did the arrest
involve insults or beatings?

101
00:05:17,383 --> 00:05:19,688
Or even kicking you with their
feet? Or was it a routine arrest?

102
00:05:20,007 --> 00:05:23,406
They made us bow our heads

103
00:05:26,352 --> 00:05:27,438
And our hands were
shackled behind us

104
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,711
And we walked one after another

105
00:05:31,719 --> 00:05:34,148
Interviewer: Wasn't there any
cursing or beating with that?

106
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:35,703
Yes, they beat us

107
00:05:35,828 --> 00:05:36,453
Interviewer: On the way?

108
00:05:36,484 --> 00:05:37,039
Yes
